-- Reid wants to finish up Wall St bill today
-- 
-- Thu Jul 15, 2010 9:48am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/07/15/us-financial-reform-votes-idUSTRE66E31120100715

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The top Democrat in the U.S. Senate on Thursday said he wants to hold a final vote on a sweeping overhaul of financial regulations in the afternoon after a key procedural vote takes place at roughly 11 a.m. EDT. 

 "We would like to ... complete action the on Wall Street reform legislation today," Democratic Leader Harry Reid said on the Senate floor. In order for a vote to take place today, Reid needs to cooperation of Republicans, who largely oppose the bill. (Reporting by  Andy Sullivan ; Editing by Theodore d'Afflisio)